Title: Nana

reviewText: NanaI first saw this movie about 8 years ago on Comcast free HD movies on demand and have been searching for a cheap VHS copy ever since. I've never been able to find it for under $50 used and my limit is $20 for a used copy of this movie. I see that it has been released on Laserdisc many years ago, so why no DVD or Blu-Ray?Katya Berger is one of the more beautiful women in the world in my opinion, but I just watched this movie again for the first time in 8 years through Netflix in HD and I must say that even as beautiful of a face and body she has, the character "Nana" she plays is really selfish, manipulitave and destructive to everyone she comes in contact with, I guess I was just stunned by her beauty and not thinking of some of the moral issues here. On the other hand I could see that all these guys lives she ruined had it coming to them for lusting after her and allowing her to take control of and destroy there lives. They should have known better or had more self control.My search for this movie at a decent price on VHS is over, I'll either catch it on Comcast when it comes back around or Netflix for however long they decide to keep it in the movie que. I would like to buy this movie if it ever comes out on dvd or Blu-Ray though. I give this movie 5 stars just for the stunning beauty of Katya Berger alone.All in all I would say that there is a lot more that could have been done with this movie and it is a shame that this looks like the last movie Katya Berger made. A better but more controversial movie she made before Nana was a Spanish movie titled Piccole Labbra from 1978.
summary: Katya Berger is beautiful for sure, a face and body to die for.
Title: Nana
